ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: super interesting. the readings are great and informative, probably more so than class time. though there is way too much reading. it is unnecessarily excessive considering we just go over the exact same stuff in class.
It's a decent amount of reading but it's important material to know and you learn a lot about the healthcare system.

It's an ok class. A bit stressful since the final is 50% of your grade and the essay questions really just can't be answered properly in that time frame. Lectures aren't the most engaging, and overall the class lacks structure, but the material taught is good.

The information and readings were very interesting, and I would recommend the course if you plan on doing the readings, but not necessarily otherwise. The workload is extremely light, so if you are looking for a gut, this could be a good class.
yeah, I'd recommend the course. It was interesting and is important stuff to know, even if you're not going into the health professions or into politics.
